result.execSummary:
The defendant Tina L. Primeaux was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged or terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of any restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Must pay all costs of supervision and court ordered financial obligations during the term of probation.
Obtain and maintain employment commensurate with her treatment needs, at her agent's direction.

The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.

Work with her agent and the Jackson County Child Support Agency to determine a proper method to pay arrears and determine a managable and reasonable paymemt plan for payment of child support obligations.  

Credit for 84 days, if revoked.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant plead guilty to the charge in the information.    Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  She understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. She understood. Felony warnings given.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Failure to Support Child (120 Days+) contrary to 948.22(2).  Joint recommendation for:  Probation, 2 years.  May discharge early if she becomes compliant.  Cooperate with CSA to make attempts to become current on her account.  To be determined by CSA and her agent.  Regular payment plan.  Credit for 84 days.  Pay extradition costs $571.40.  Defendant did not exercise her right to allocution.

Court ordered sentence withheld, 2 years probation.  Work with the of the Child Support Agency and her Agent to determine a proper method to take care of arrears,  determine a manageable and reasonable payment plan.    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  CC.  Extradition costs.    Court advised defendant of the DNA submission requirement.  Obtain and maintain employment commensurate with her treatment needs, at her agent's direction.  Credit for 84 days, if revoked.
